.TH "HTMLTextAreaElement.select_event" "JS" "July 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLTextAreaElement.select_event \- HTMLTextAreaElement: select event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]select\f[B]\f[R] event fires when some text has been
selected.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]select\[dq], (event) => {});

onselect = (event) => {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Selection logger
.IP
.EX
<textarea>Try selecting some text in this element.</textarea>
<p id=\[dq]log\[dq]></p>
.EE
.IP
.EX
function logSelection(event) {
  const log = document.getElementById(\[dq]log\[dq]);
  const selection = event.target.value.substring(
    event.target.selectionStart,
    event.target.selectionEnd,
  );
  log.textContent = \[ga]You selected: ${selection}\[ga];
}

const textarea = document.querySelector(\[dq]textarea\[dq]);
textarea.addEventListener(\[dq]select\[dq], logSelection);
.EE
.SS onselect equivalent
You can also set up the event handler using the \f[CR]onselect\f[R]
property:
.IP
.EX
textarea.onselect = logSelection;
.EE
